docs.lead_paragraph: Quiet conditions prevailed in the foreign exchange market last week. Business was in small volume and the daily range of rates limited to narrow lines. The dullness was ascribed to the absence of pressure from Europe's political and financial problems which had hitherto provoked erratic changes and volume turnover, also to the observance of Holy Week in the foreign capitals.

headline.main: FOREIGN EXCHANGE RATES; WEEK ENDED APRIL 20, 1935.
